What is LVM?
Logical Volume Manager allows flexible disk management.

Components:
Physical Volume (PV)
Volume Group (VG)
Logical Volume (LV)

Filesystem:
Create Physical Volume
pvcreate /dev/xvdf

Create Volume Group:
vgcreate devops_vg /dev/xvdf

Create Logical Volume:
lvcreate -L 5G -n app_lv devops_vg

Extend Volume:
lvextend -L +2G /dev/devops_vg/app_lv

Resize Filesystem:
resize2fs /dev/devops_vg/app_lv

Real-Time Scenario:
Application requires more storage without downtime.
Use LVM extension instead of adding new mount points.
